name: Sunset Point, Coffee shop (KAK OMAN)
address: Bukit Tumpeng, Lalanglinggah, Kec. Selemadeg Bar., Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
Santa and his whole family are amazing people.
We went there looking for some nice coffee and a guide to take us to the waterfall. What was supposed to be a quick stop ended up in a great experience for us. We were able to see the sunset , enjoy amazing food and even sing laraope with the locals that gather there.
We didn't want to leave and were sad when we did. We had such an amazing experience and would love to do it again
Thank you so much Mister and Miss Santa for being such awesome people and making us feel part of your family
review 2:
Very nice spot. Fantastic view. Coffee is good. Bintang even better. It is a fantastic view of the sea and mountains.
Definitely worth coming to see the views.
review 3: Most beautiful view in Bali, and thats sating something. Charming little place woth food, snacks and the best view you will see.
review 4: Beautiful spot with a terrace with stunning views over the hills, forests and ocean. Friendly people serve nice cold Bintangs here.
review 5: Beauty place on top of Bukit Tumpeng village,, must visit this place!!

name: PT Eka Surya Waterfall
address: GWVV+PR, Lalanglinggah, Selemadeg Barat, Tabanan Regency, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
The waterfall is just amazing, and Eka is really nice. You definitely need to ask him to guide you, as the way is down the cliffs pretty much, on ladders and steps
But the spot after is so rewarding, and the swim so good!

Highly recommend!!
review 2: The waterfall was soooo beautiful and eke was really nice and helpful he even helped us buying some fresh vanilla afterwards.
review 3:
Good guide, speaks a good English and even made me try durian fruit !
Thanks Eka and your parents for your time !
